The paper deals with Visual QA, which involves understanding language and vision, and requires complex relational reasoning. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, computer vision and natural language processing are the most likely sub-categories, as they are directly related to the tasks involved in Visual QA.
